Text.SourceString: *laughs uncontrollably*

Text.SourceString: People should always tell the truth because keeping track of lies is hard. It’s easier to just be who we are.
Text.LocalizedString: People should always tell the truth because keeping track of lies is hard. It’s easier to just be who we are.

Text.LocalizedString: So, have you got any truths for me, <PlayerName>$player</>? Let’s hear it.

Text.SourceString: When one of my clients has a bad idea, I tell them.//I don’t want them walking around town with bad hair and people thinking it’s my fault!
Text.LocalizedString: When one of my clients has a bad idea, I tell them.//I don’t want them walking around town with bad hair and people thinking it’s my fault!

Text.SourceString: Looking gorgeous as usual – just like an iris!//<portrait=happy>Ah, I love irises. *winks*
Text.LocalizedString: Looking gorgeous as usual – just like an iris!//<portrait=happy>Ah, I love irises. *winks*

Text.SourceString: She and <NpcName>Sam</> are the cutest couple. They’re such sweethearts!

Text.LocalizedString: I love catching up with <NpcName>Ben</>. He always has insightful things to say.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Ben</> gets around, you know. He usually disappears the last two weeks of Fall.//<portrait=surprised>Who knows where he goes?
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Ben</> gets around, you know. He usually disappears the last two weeks of Fall.//<portrait=surprised>Who knows where he goes?

Text.LocalizedString: I don’t go to the lake or wherever. Places like that are just too quiet for me.

Text.SourceString: I’ll totally lose my mind if I’m left alone with my thoughts for too long. *chuckles*
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll totally lose my mind if I’m left alone with my thoughts for too long. *chuckles*

Text.LocalizedString: Could you imagine running this town on your own?//Oh, Mayor <NpcName>Connor</> is good at it. We love him.

Text.LocalizedString: My goodness. The islanders are hard to keep up with!

Text.SourceString: Don’t you just love <NpcName>Karen’s</> haircut? The lady working at Pufferfish.//<portrait=happy>That was me. I did that!
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t you just love <NpcName>Karen’s</> haircut? The lady working at Pufferfish.//<portrait=happy>That was me. I did that!

Text.SourceString: Can you believe it’s the weekend already?
Text.LocalizedString: Can you believe it’s the weekend already?

Text.SourceString: Well, not quite the weekend yet, but almost. It’s Thursday, which means tomorrow is Friday.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, not quite the weekend yet, but almost. It’s Thursday, which means tomorrow is Friday.

Text.LocalizedString: What do I do on the weekends? Hmm. That’s a great question.

Text.LocalizedString: I help clean up the community center.//The place is often empty. You wouldn’t believe how dusty it gets.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I work on Sundays. If there’s nothing better to do, that is.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I work on Sundays. If there’s nothing better to do, that is.

Text.SourceString: Oh, no, I’m not worried about break-ins. I just don’t want any visitors.//<portrait=normal>Besides, <NpcName>Frank</> has his own key, so he can let himself into the house whenever.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, no, I’m not worried about break-ins. I just don’t want any visitors.//<portrait=normal>Besides, <NpcName>Frank</> has his own key, so he can let himself into the house whenever.

Text.LocalizedString: Oh, no, no. I don’t gossip. I extract and share information.//<portrait=happy><Italic>Yes!</> Sort of like the morning news.

Text.SourceString: I’m doing a public service, making sure we all know who our neighbors are. It’s not an easy job, you know. Never once have I been thanked.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m doing a public service, making sure we all know who our neighbors are. It’s not an easy job, you know. Never once have I been thanked.

Text.SourceString: Having a job and all doesn’t leave me with much time to keep up with the neighbors.
Text.LocalizedString: Having a job and all doesn’t leave me with much time to keep up with the neighbors.

Text.SourceString: One time when I was sick, everyone started going through these massive life changes. By the time I was back on my feet, there was a new scientist in town, a huge corporation was trying to drill up the island, and <NpcName>Valentina’s</> dad had missed a visit!

Text.SourceString: *chuckles* Excuse me for prying.

Text.LocalizedString: People should always tell the truth because, gosh! Lies are hard to remember.//Also, I don’t wanna be caught spreading false information. My good name is on the line.

Text.LocalizedString: The man loves that job. It would probably break his heart if anybody else did it.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Charles</> does have red hair, but he also colors it red to keep it bright.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Charles</> does have red hair, but he also colors it red to keep it bright.

Text.SourceString: If you ask me, I’d say it’s because the poor thing wants a bit of brightness in his life.
Text.LocalizedString: If you ask me, I’d say it’s because the poor thing wants a bit of brightness in his life.

Text.SourceString: Here comes Summer!
Text.LocalizedString: Here comes Summer!

Text.SourceString: With all this humidity, it’s going to be one sweaty Summer for us.
Text.LocalizedString: With all this humidity, it’s going to be one sweaty Summer for us.

Text.SourceString: I still volunteer at the school. Summer, Fall… All year round.
Text.LocalizedString: I still volunteer at the school. Summer, Fall… All year round.

Text.SourceString: Has Summer been kind to you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//We left some food on the counter last night, and one of the cats ate it.
Text.LocalizedString: Has Summer been kind to you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//We left some food on the counter last night, and one of the cats ate it.

Text.SourceString: So now I’m just keeping an eye on <NPCName>Peanut</> and my baby, <NPCName>Butter</>. Hopefully, nobody gets a tummy ache.
Text.LocalizedString: So now I’m just keeping an eye on <NPCName>Peanut</> and my baby, <NPCName>Butter</>. Hopefully, nobody gets a tummy ache.

Text.SourceString: I’m going right home as soon as I’m done with work. I have to keep an eye on the cats tonight.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going right home as soon as I’m done with work. I have to keep an eye on the cats tonight.

Text.SourceString: I caught them trying to open the fridge this morning. I’m not about to let that go.

Text.LocalizedString: I’m going right home as soon as I’m done with work. I’m feeling a little sick today.

Text.SourceString: I think I should eat some soup and lie down.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I should eat some soup and lie down.

Text.SourceString: Do you have one of those calendars in your house, <PlayerName>$player</>?//You can keep track of people’s birthdays at your convenience.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have one of those calendars in your house, <PlayerName>$player</>?//You can keep track of people’s birthdays at your convenience.

Text.SourceString: My good friend <NpcName>Bree’s</> birthday is coming up. I’m gonna see if I have some jackfruit lying around.//She loves that stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: My good friend <NpcName>Bree’s</> birthday is coming up. I’m gonna see if I have some jackfruit lying around.//She loves that stuff.

Text.SourceString: If not, I guess a jar of jam will do.
Text.LocalizedString: If not, I guess a jar of jam will do.

Text.SourceString: I have <NpcName>Ben</> looking out for orchids this Fall.//I hope he comes through.
Text.LocalizedString: I have <NpcName>Ben</> looking out for orchids this Fall.//I hope he comes through.

Text.SourceString: The thing about Winter, though, is not a lot of people are out and about.//It’s hard to socialize when we’re all cooped up in our houses.
Text.LocalizedString: The thing about Winter, though, is not a lot of people are out and about.//It’s hard to socialize when we’re all cooped up in our houses.

Text.SourceString: You know, <NpcName>Bree</> came from a big city, just like you. She had a fancy modeling job right before she married <NpcName>Walter</>.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, <NpcName>Bree</> came from a big city, just like you. She had a fancy modeling job right before she married <NpcName>Walter</>.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to the Winter Fair on Sunday.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to the Winter Fair on Sunday.

Text.SourceString: I have some business to take care of on Saturday, so I can’t go then. But I heard <NpcName>Sam</> and <NpcName>Emily</> will be there.
Text.LocalizedString: I have some business to take care of on Saturday, so I can’t go then. But I heard <NpcName>Sam</> and <NpcName>Emily</> will be there.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Frank</> said I’d make a great detective.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Frank</> said I’d make a great detective.

Text.SourceString: I know he was teasing me, but I have to agree with him. *chuckles* I was flattered.
Text.LocalizedString: I know he was teasing me, but I have to agree with him. *chuckles* I was flattered.

Text.LocalizedString: Rainy days make me so hungry, for some reason. You too, yeah?

Text.SourceString: So annoying. I have things to do, you know. I can’t sit and eat all day.
Text.LocalizedString: So annoying. I have things to do, you know. I can’t sit and eat all day.

Text.SourceString: Perfect weather for some spicy red curry!
Text.LocalizedString: Perfect weather for some spicy red curry!

Text.LocalizedString: The cats hate the rain. Now that I think about it, they don’t really like sunshine either. Hmm.

Text.SourceString: Watch your step! It’s super slippery.
Text.LocalizedString: Watch your step! It’s super slippery.

Text.SourceString: Did I ever tell you about my first date with <NpcName>Frank</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Did I ever tell you about my first date with <NpcName>Frank</>?

Text.SourceString: Oh, good fairies! Here comes a story.//<portrait=normal>He took me on a picnic. When the big day came, it was storming really hard.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, good fairies! Here comes a story.//<portrait=normal>He took me on a picnic. When the big day came, it was storming really hard.

Text.SourceString: Storming just like this. But we didn’t wanna cancel, because it was our first date.//<portrait=normal>I was curious about him. When we got to the picnic spot, we stood under a tree to stay dry.//And he went on and on telling stories, trying to keep me interested.
Text.LocalizedString: Storming just like this. But we didn’t wanna cancel, because it was our first date.//<portrait=normal>I was curious about him. When we got to the picnic spot, we stood under a tree to stay dry.//And he went on and on telling stories, trying to keep me interested.

Text.SourceString: I was so busy listening to his story, trying to follow what he was saying – mind you, it was storming! – that we both forgot to keep an eye on the picnic basket.//<portrait=surprised>It blew away! We had <Italic>no</> food.
Text.LocalizedString: I was so busy listening to his story, trying to follow what he was saying – mind you, it was storming! – that we both forgot to keep an eye on the picnic basket.//<portrait=surprised>It blew away! We had <Italic>no</> food.

Text.SourceString: Oh, you silly goose! Of course you wanna hear a story.//<portrait=surprised>Oh! Here comes a story. He took me on a picnic.//<portrait=normal>When the big day came, it was storming really hard.

Text.LocalizedString: Storming just like this. But we didn’t wanna cancel, because it was our first date.//<portrait=normal>I was curious about him. When we got to the picnic spot, we stood under a tree to stay dry.//And he went on and on telling stories, trying to keep me interested.

Text.SourceString: The cats hate the rain.//Now that I think about it, they don’t really like sunshine either. Hmm.
Text.LocalizedString: The cats hate the rain.//Now that I think about it, they don’t really like sunshine either. Hmm.

Text.SourceString: It is one windy day! Cover your head, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: It is one windy day! Cover your head, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: I should’ve worn my hat.
Text.LocalizedString: I should’ve worn my hat.

Text.SourceString: It’s so windy out.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so windy out.

Text.SourceString: The snow is kinda pretty, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: The snow is kinda pretty, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: My favorite winter spot is next to a fireplace.//Bet it’s yours too!
Text.LocalizedString: My favorite winter spot is next to a fireplace.//Bet it’s yours too!

Text.SourceString: Ahh! It’s so cold! I’m ready for Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Ahh! It’s so cold! I’m ready for Summer.

Text.SourceString: You can still grow things like snowdrops and tea plants, right?
Text.LocalizedString: You can still grow things like snowdrops and tea plants, right?

Text.SourceString: Ahh! It’s so cold! I’m ready for Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Ahh! It’s so cold! I’m ready for Summer.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Kenny</> mentioned that more animals get sick when it snows. Are your animals doing okay?
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Kenny</> mentioned that more animals get sick when it snows. Are your animals doing okay?

Text.SourceString: Hopefully, the cats won’t go out today. It’s way too cold for them.
Text.LocalizedString: Hopefully, the cats won’t go out today. It’s way too cold for them.

Text.SourceString: The snow makes everything look so clean.
Text.LocalizedString: The snow makes everything look so clean.

Text.SourceString: Ahh! It’s so cold! I’m ready for Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Ahh! It’s so cold! I’m ready for Summer.

Text.SourceString: *shivers*
Text.LocalizedString: *shivers*

Text.SourceString: I volunteer here once a week. Usually on Mondays.//I have fewer clients at the salon early in the week, so Mondays are perfect for me.
Text.LocalizedString: I volunteer here once a week. Usually on Mondays.//I have fewer clients at the salon early in the week, so Mondays are perfect for me.

Text.SourceString: I think I have wood chips in my shoes.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I have wood chips in my shoes.

Text.SourceString: It’s inevitable.//<portrait=concerned>Every time I walk here, wood chips, wood chips, wood chips!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s inevitable.//<portrait=concerned>Every time I walk here, wood chips, wood chips, wood chips!

Text.SourceString: You know <NpcName>Dippa</>? The painter? They used to perform in some sort of acrobatic group.
Text.LocalizedString: You know <NpcName>Dippa</>? The painter? They used to perform in some sort of acrobatic group.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think they do anymore. They threw their back out or something.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think they do anymore. They threw their back out or something.

Text.SourceString: I’m just enjoying the weather. What are you doing, <PlayerName>$player</>? You look like you’re in a rush.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m just enjoying the weather. What are you doing, <PlayerName>$player</>? You look like you’re in a rush.

Text.SourceString: I always wonder why <NpcName>Bree</> didn’t buy your grandparents’ land.//<portrait=surprised>She seems to be at the lookout all the time. So she <Italic>clearly</> enjoys the view from up there.
Text.LocalizedString: I always wonder why <NpcName>Bree</> didn’t buy your grandparents’ land.//<portrait=surprised>She seems to be at the lookout all the time. So she <Italic>clearly</> enjoys the view from up there.

Text.SourceString: It’s a mystery to me, because the lady has money.//<portrait=happy>But hey, at least now we have you.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a mystery to me, because the lady has money.//<portrait=happy>But hey, at least now we have you.

Text.SourceString: Don’t be silly. I’m not snooping around.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t be silly. I’m not snooping around.

Text.SourceString: I’m merely enjoying the town. If there happens to be some information I can pick up, that’s just a happy coincidence.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m merely enjoying the town. If there happens to be some information I can pick up, that’s just a happy coincidence.

Text.SourceString: You can get really good at cooking just by watching the cooking channel. So many super easy recipes.
Text.LocalizedString: You can get really good at cooking just by watching the cooking channel. So many super easy recipes.

Text.SourceString: I don’t cook too well. Anything beyond a simple salad is out of my league.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t cook too well. Anything beyond a simple salad is out of my league.

Text.SourceString: I’m not looking forward to going home. Nobody did the dishes before we left this morning.//<portrait=normal>So the house is a huge mess right now.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not looking forward to going home. Nobody did the dishes before we left this morning.//<portrait=normal>So the house is a huge mess right now.

Text.SourceString: I can’t make everybody look good, <PlayerName>$player</>! I’m not a magician.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t make everybody look good, <PlayerName>$player</>! I’m not a magician.

Text.SourceString: But I can work on your hair. That’s a great canvas you’ve got.
Text.LocalizedString: But I can work on your hair. That’s a great canvas you’ve got.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> need to go outside more. They love their sofas too much.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> need to go outside more. They love their sofas too much.

Text.SourceString: This one time, I gave <NpcName>Dippa</> hot cocoa for their birthday because I didn’t have anything else ready.
Text.LocalizedString: This one time, I gave <NpcName>Dippa</> hot cocoa for their birthday because I didn’t have anything else ready.

Text.SourceString: And frankly, if I’m being honest, I forgot.//<portrait=happy>But it turned out to be one of their favorite things!//<portrait=normal>I got lucky, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: And frankly, if I’m being honest, I forgot.//<portrait=happy>But it turned out to be one of their favorite things!//<portrait=normal>I got lucky, I guess.

Text.SourceString: Who would’ve thought I’d see you here! Of all places.
Text.LocalizedString: Who would’ve thought I’d see you here! Of all places.

Text.SourceString: You can count on me for a good haircut.//So, if you ever want to change…umm…that, just drop by the salon.
Text.LocalizedString: You can count on me for a good haircut.//So, if you ever want to change…umm…that, just drop by the salon.

Text.SourceString: This building is old. As old as the town, I believe.//<portrait=happy>It doesn’t look like it though, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: This building is old. As old as the town, I believe.//<portrait=happy>It doesn’t look like it though, huh?

Text.SourceString: I think the Tavern is the only building as old as this one.
Text.LocalizedString: I think the Tavern is the only building as old as this one.

Text.SourceString: I’m here to promote my salon. Haircut, hair color. You know the drill.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m here to promote my salon. Haircut, hair color. You know the drill.

Text.SourceString: Oh, imagine if people started coming to this island just to go to my salon!/<portrait=normal>Just thinking about it makes me excited!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, imagine if people started coming to this island just to go to my salon!/<portrait=normal>Just thinking about it makes me excited!

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Emily</> should really come here with me sometime. We could have a chat over cheese.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Emily</> should really come here with me sometime. We could have a chat over cheese.

Text.SourceString: Make sure to check in on Stephen! He’s a delight, with his little claws.//So cute.
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure to check in on Stephen! He’s a delight, with his little claws.//So cute.

Text.SourceString: What a smart idea to put a sewing machine out here, huh?//So kind.
Text.LocalizedString: What a smart idea to put a sewing machine out here, huh?//So kind.

Text.SourceString: Don’t be silly, <PlayerName>$player</>! I’m not snooping around.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t be silly, <PlayerName>$player</>! I’m not snooping around.

Text.SourceString: I’m here to check on my friends and see what they’ve been up to.//<portrait=surprised>And you know, to see what’s going on with <NpcName>Antonio</> lately.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m here to check on my friends and see what they’ve been up to.//<portrait=surprised>And you know, to see what’s going on with <NpcName>Antonio</> lately.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Antonio</> is <NpcName>Valentina’s</> dad. <NpcName>Rafael’s</> cousin.//<portrait=annoyed>Keep up, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Antonio</> is <NpcName>Valentina’s</> dad. <NpcName>Rafael’s</> cousin.//<portrait=annoyed>Keep up, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: Ooh… What are you doing coming here so often?
Text.LocalizedString: Ooh… What are you doing coming here so often?

Text.SourceString: Don’t worry! My lips are sealed.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t worry! My lips are sealed.

Text.SourceString: My aunt told me that a long time ago, when she was a little girl, she and her friends used to watch the area around the villa at midnight to see if there was actually a ghost living there.
Text.LocalizedString: My aunt told me that a long time ago, when she was a little girl, she and her friends used to watch the area around the villa at midnight to see if there was actually a ghost living there.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, this was before the villa was even built.//My nana would get upset because Aunt Abel would stay up too late. Do you believe in that sort of stuff, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, this was before the villa was even built.//My nana would get upset because Aunt Abel would stay up too late. Do you believe in that sort of stuff, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Today is <NpcName>Frank’s</> birthday. *whispers* I got him a gift.//I’m gonna give it to him later, when we get home.
Text.LocalizedString: Today is <NpcName>Frank’s</> birthday. *whispers* I got him a gift.//I’m gonna give it to him later, when we get home.

Text.SourceString: Drinks on me, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Drinks on me, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: To <NpcName>Frank</>!
Text.LocalizedString: To <NpcName>Frank</>!

Text.SourceString: All right. Keep being you, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: All right. Keep being you, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Special.SourceString: Nah. Thanks, though. I still have work.
Special.LocalizedString: Nah. Thanks, though. I still have work.

Text.SourceString: It smells a bit musky here, doesn’t it? Like sandalwood.
Text.LocalizedString: It smells a bit musky here, doesn’t it? Like sandalwood.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Betty</> said it’s the smell of good times and old friends.//I think she’s right.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Betty</> said it’s the smell of good times and old friends.//I think she’s right.

Text.SourceString: Being an adult is mostly just washing dishes nonstop.
Text.LocalizedString: Being an adult is mostly just washing dishes nonstop.

Text.SourceString: I’m not looking forward to going home. Nobody did the dishes this morning before we left.//<portrait=normal>So the house is a huge mess right now.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not looking forward to going home. Nobody did the dishes this morning before we left.//<portrait=normal>So the house is a huge mess right now.

Text.SourceString: Being an adult is mostly just washing dishes nonstop.
Text.LocalizedString: Being an adult is mostly just washing dishes nonstop.

Text.SourceString: Once you sit down on one of these sofas, it’s hard to get up.//<portrait=concerned>I get why these cats don’t like going outside.
Text.LocalizedString: Once you sit down on one of these sofas, it’s hard to get up.//<portrait=concerned>I get why these cats don’t like going outside.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Frank</> often works late, so I usually get to hog the TV all night.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Frank</> often works late, so I usually get to hog the TV all night.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll go to bed soon.//It’s been a long day. I could use some extra sleep.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll go to bed soon.//It’s been a long day. I could use some extra sleep.

Text.SourceString: My request? Just follow through and bring something good for the potluck.
Text.LocalizedString: My request? Just follow through and bring something good for the potluck.

Text.SourceString: Thank you, <PlayerName>$player</>. I know I can count on you. Dinner tonight is going to be special.
Text.LocalizedString: Thank you, <PlayerName>$player</>. I know I can count on you. Dinner tonight is going to be special.

Text.SourceString: I saw <NpcName>Bree</> wearing a very fancy-looking sweater. White cashmere. I’m sure it’s very expensive.//<portrait=surprised>It had something fussy on it, almost like <Italic>fur</>!
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NpcName>Bree</> wearing a very fancy-looking sweater. White cashmere. I’m sure it’s very expensive.//<portrait=surprised>It had something fussy on it, almost like <Italic>fur</>!

Text.SourceString: Do you think it’s actually real fur? I sure hope not.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think it’s actually real fur? I sure hope not.

Text.SourceString: Did you hear about <NpcName>Leah’s</> mom missing her birthday again?//<portrait=surprised>Not even a call. Oof! That lady.//<portrait=concerned>Poor thing only got a present she’d sent. A new dress, I heard.
Text.LocalizedString: Did you hear about <NpcName>Leah’s</> mom missing her birthday again?//<portrait=surprised>Not even a call. Oof! That lady.//<portrait=concerned>Poor thing only got a present she’d sent. A new dress, I heard.

Text.SourceString: Her mom even sent the present <Italic>weeks</> late.//Oof! That’s ice-cold.
Text.LocalizedString: Her mom even sent the present <Italic>weeks</> late.//Oof! That’s ice-cold.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Ling</>? Are you asking me about <NpcName>Ling</>?//<portrait=normal>I don’t know anything worth mentioning, to be honest with you.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, except…
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Ling</>? Are you asking me about <NpcName>Ling</>?//<portrait=normal>I don’t know anything worth mentioning, to be honest with you.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, except…

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Betty</> told me a long time ago that she arrived here with a box full of gold.//That’s how she got the mansion. Not money, not credit. Gold.//<portrait=annoyed>Those solid-gold coins – you know what I’m talking about?
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Betty</> told me a long time ago that she arrived here with a box full of gold.//That’s how she got the mansion. Not money, not credit. Gold.//<portrait=annoyed>Those solid-gold coins – you know what I’m talking about?

Text.SourceString: I love buying cat furniture. I can tell <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> are grateful.
Text.LocalizedString: I love buying cat furniture. I can tell <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> are grateful.

Text.SourceString: I wish <NpcName>Joko</> would carry more options, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish <NpcName>Joko</> would carry more options, though.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Frank</> and I dated in high school.//We parted ways after graduation. I wanted to study cosmetology, so we went to different schools.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Frank</> and I dated in high school.//We parted ways after graduation. I wanted to study cosmetology, so we went to different schools.

Text.SourceString: We rekindled, though, obviously. *laughs*
Text.LocalizedString: We rekindled, though, obviously. *laughs*

Text.SourceString: You got any news for me, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//<portrait=normal>Some weekend news, <Italic>maaaaaybe</>?
Text.LocalizedString: You got any news for me, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//<portrait=normal>Some weekend news, <Italic>maaaaaybe</>?

Text.SourceString: What about <NpcName>Luke</>? I heard you two are friends.//<portrait=normal>I can never get anything out of that boy.
Text.LocalizedString: What about <NpcName>Luke</>? I heard you two are friends.//<portrait=normal>I can never get anything out of that boy.

Text.SourceString: I woke up thinking about the kids this morning. Just a rush of excitement out of nowhere.//I can’t wait to see them again next week.
Text.LocalizedString: I woke up thinking about the kids this morning. Just a rush of excitement out of nowhere.//I can’t wait to see them again next week.

Text.SourceString: People have been complaining left and right about <NPCName>Peanut</> and my baby, <NPCName>Butter</>.//They’re cats. They wander.//<portrait=sad>Oh well, I’m gonna make sure my cats don’t go around waking people up at midnight. Don’t worry.
Text.LocalizedString: People have been complaining left and right about <NPCName>Peanut</> and my baby, <NPCName>Butter</>.//They’re cats. They wander.//<portrait=sad>Oh well, I’m gonna make sure my cats don’t go around waking people up at midnight. Don’t worry.

Text.SourceString: I don’t blame <NpcName>Suki</> for getting upset that <NpcName>Antonio</> only visits <NpcName>Valentina</> on weekends.//<portrait=normal>Kids need attention from both parents. Right?
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t blame <NpcName>Suki</> for getting upset that <NpcName>Antonio</> only visits <NpcName>Valentina</> on weekends.//<portrait=normal>Kids need attention from both parents. Right?

Text.SourceString: All in all, <NpcName>Antonio</> is a good dad. I’ll give him that.//He always tries to be in his baby’s life, despite the distance and all that.
Text.LocalizedString: All in all, <NpcName>Antonio</> is a good dad. I’ll give him that.//He always tries to be in his baby’s life, despite the distance and all that.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, I don’t know how I feel about them. I love them both.//Just trying to be a supportive friend here, <PlayerName>$player</>. But I can see why they didn’t work out.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, I don’t know how I feel about them. I love them both.//Just trying to be a supportive friend here, <PlayerName>$player</>. But I can see why they didn’t work out.

Text.SourceString: So, the rumor around town is you’re getting close to everybody. Giving folks gifts and such?
Text.LocalizedString: So, the rumor around town is you’re getting close to everybody. Giving folks gifts and such?

Text.SourceString: Ooh! Look at you, the social Butterfly.//<portrait=normal>We need to keep each other up to speed.
Text.LocalizedString: Ooh! Look at you, the social Butterfly.//<portrait=normal>We need to keep each other up to speed.

Text.SourceString: I should’ve worn my hat.
Text.LocalizedString: I should’ve worn my hat.

Text.SourceString: I should’ve worn my hat.//<portrait=annoyed>You have white stuff on your shoulder. Is that snow or…?
Text.LocalizedString: I should’ve worn my hat.//<portrait=annoyed>You have white stuff on your shoulder. Is that snow or…?

Text.SourceString: I should’ve worn my hat.
Text.LocalizedString: I should’ve worn my hat.

Text.SourceString: You’d think soup would be a bad idea in this weather, wouldn’t you? But nope!//<portrait=happy>I had red curry for lunch yesterday. Lunch! And it was as delicious as ever.
Text.LocalizedString: You’d think soup would be a bad idea in this weather, wouldn’t you? But nope!//<portrait=happy>I had red curry for lunch yesterday. Lunch! And it was as delicious as ever.

Text.SourceString: That might just be because my husband’s a great cook, though. *winks*
Text.LocalizedString: That might just be because my husband’s a great cook, though. *winks*

Text.SourceString: We got new products at the salon last week.//<portrait=concerned>Great line, makes hair soft and shiny, but the smell… Yuck!
Text.LocalizedString: We got new products at the salon last week.//<portrait=concerned>Great line, makes hair soft and shiny, but the smell… Yuck!

Text.SourceString: It smells like… I wanna say, wet socks.//Yep, definitely wet socks.
Text.LocalizedString: It smells like… I wanna say, wet socks.//Yep, definitely wet socks.

Text.SourceString: I like seeing the kids playing outdoors in Winter. I saw them take the class outside the other day.//<portrait=happy>They should get out there more, play in the snow!
Text.LocalizedString: I like seeing the kids playing outdoors in Winter. I saw them take the class outside the other day.//<portrait=happy>They should get out there more, play in the snow!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> hate clothes.//<portrait=annoyed>I wanna put sweaters on them. You know, ’cause it’s Winter.//They crawl right out of them. It’s become a hazard, really, the clothes.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> hate clothes.//<portrait=annoyed>I wanna put sweaters on them. You know, ’cause it’s Winter.//They crawl right out of them. It’s become a hazard, really, the clothes.

Text.SourceString: I give up. They seem fine so far.
Text.LocalizedString: I give up. They seem fine so far.

Text.SourceString: Funny, I don’t like to color my hair now.//I used to do it in my twenties. All kinds of styles. Pink ombre, pastel colors… But I think I’ve found my style now.
Text.LocalizedString: Funny, I don’t like to color my hair now.//I used to do it in my twenties. All kinds of styles. Pink ombre, pastel colors… But I think I’ve found my style now.

Text.SourceString: Besides, I colored it way too much. It might have started falling out if I didn’t rest it for a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: Besides, I colored it way too much. It might have started falling out if I didn’t rest it for a bit.

Text.SourceString: That’s it! I’m wearing my hair up the whole season.//I <Italic>hate</> sweating.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s it! I’m wearing my hair up the whole season.//I <Italic>hate</> sweating.

Text.SourceString: Since Fishensips is the only bar here, you’d think it’d be a lot busier during the day.
Text.LocalizedString: Since Fishensips is the only bar here, you’d think it’d be a lot busier during the day.

Text.SourceString: Oh, right! I forgot about the Beach Shack.//<portrait=normal>You’re right. Some people might like it better.//It’s right there on the beach, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, right! I forgot about the Beach Shack.//<portrait=normal>You’re right. Some people might like it better.//It’s right there on the beach, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Betty</> can go overboard when it comes to <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>.//She makes these lavish gourmet meals for them.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Betty</> can go overboard when it comes to <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</>.//She makes these lavish gourmet meals for them.

Text.SourceString: I suppose because <NpcName>Frank</> and I don’t have kids, <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> are her grandbabies.
Text.LocalizedString: I suppose because <NpcName>Frank</> and I don’t have kids, <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> are her grandbabies.

Text.SourceString: I saw <NpcName>Taco</> swimming around in Winter.//Oh, you know, all Winter – in the fountain.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw <NpcName>Taco</> swimming around in Winter.//Oh, you know, all Winter – in the fountain.

Text.SourceString: That dog must be half bear!
Text.LocalizedString: That dog must be half bear!

Text.SourceString: I yawned too wide this morning. Almost got my jaw stuck.//It still kind of hurts.
Text.LocalizedString: I yawned too wide this morning. Almost got my jaw stuck.//It still kind of hurts.

Text.SourceString: Walking in heels in this heat sure feels like a workout.//<portrait=happy>Don’t be shocked, you! The next time you see me, my quads might be as big as my baby, <NPCName>Butter</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Walking in heels in this heat sure feels like a workout.//<portrait=happy>Don’t be shocked, you! The next time you see me, my quads might be as big as my baby, <NPCName>Butter</>.

Text.SourceString: I love spending time with kids.//<portrait=happy>They say the funniest things!
Text.LocalizedString: I love spending time with kids.//<portrait=happy>They say the funniest things!

Text.SourceString: No matter how much I love spending time with kids, I still don’t want my own.//I like my life the way it is.
Text.LocalizedString: No matter how much I love spending time with kids, I still don’t want my own.//I like my life the way it is.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Butter</> found a rat in our living room last night.//I guess Fall is officially here.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Butter</> found a rat in our living room last night.//I guess Fall is officially here.

Text.SourceString: I picked up a few apples from <NpcName>Sam</>’s.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, no! They aren’t for me.//<portrait=normal>They’re for the cats.
Text.LocalizedString: I picked up a few apples from <NpcName>Sam</>’s.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, no! They aren’t for me.//<portrait=normal>They’re for the cats.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Betty</> has a yummy recipe for cat treats made with apples. We’re gonna make them next Tuesday.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Betty</> has a yummy recipe for cat treats made with apples. We’re gonna make them next Tuesday.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Betty</> and I made way too many apple treats. We need to take some to share with the shelter.//They’ll love them over there.

Text.SourceString: My throat doesn’t feel so good. *coughs*//It must be all the fried tempeh I’ve been eating.
Text.LocalizedString: My throat doesn’t feel so good. *coughs*//It must be all the fried tempeh I’ve been eating.

Text.SourceString: I need to cut down on fried food.//<portrait=normal>I’ll start tomorrow. We still have some bananas left in the fridge. Gonna fry them tonight.

Text.SourceString: It’s going to be hard to top last year’s New Year’s party, but I’m sure <NpcName>Bree</> can do it.//<portrait=happy>I can’t wait to see the food. She always has the yummiest food.
